442
00:19:00,740 --> 00:19:03,007
    [ SCREECHING CONTINUES ]    

443
00:19:17,190 --> 00:19:17,922
       OH, NO.                  

444
00:19:17,924 --> 00:19:18,990
         WE'RE TRAPPED.         

445
00:19:18,992 --> 00:19:20,458
            WE DON'T HAVE TO BE.

446
00:19:20,460 --> 00:19:23,027
    [ SCREECHING CONTINUES ]    

447
00:19:32,372 --> 00:19:35,506
          REALLY, MOM,          
     I KNOW HOW TO DO THIS.     

448
00:19:35,508 --> 00:19:36,707
   NO, YOU DON'T.               

449
00:19:36,709 --> 00:19:38,676
             UGH! YES, SHE DOES.

450
00:19:38,678 --> 00:19:40,044
            SHE'S BEEN TRAINING.

451
00:19:40,046 --> 00:19:42,046
       SHE WASN'T PLAYING AROUND
              WITH THAT SWORD.  

452
00:19:42,048 --> 00:19:44,882
         SHE WAS TAKING CLASSES,
   LEARNING HOW TO USE IT RIGHT.

453
00:19:44,884 --> 00:19:46,450
                 EVEN THOUGH    
           SHE'S ALWAYS STUDYING

454
00:19:46,452 --> 00:19:48,553
            OR PRACTICING TENNIS
          OR DOING HER HOMEWORK,

455
00:19:48,555 --> 00:19:51,556
     SHE STILL WORKS REALLY HARD
     TO BE A GOOD SWORD FIGHTER.

456
00:19:51,558 --> 00:19:55,159
NO. NO, NO, NO, NO, NO, NO.     
 I KNOW MY DAUGHTER.            

457
00:19:55,161 --> 00:19:57,895
I KNOW WHAT SHE'S DOING         
EVERY SECOND OF THE DAY --      

458
00:19:57,897 --> 00:20:00,298
 ALL HER ACTIVITIES,            
 ALL HER INTERNETS.             

459
00:20:00,300 --> 00:20:03,901
I KNOW SHE'S DEFINITELY NOT     
SOME SWORD-FIGHTING HOOLIGAN.   

460
00:20:03,903 --> 00:20:05,670
        YOU DON'T KNOW ME       
             AT ALL!            

461
00:20:05,672 --> 00:20:08,739
 YOU STILL HAVEN'T EVEN NOTICED 
           MY GLASSES.          

462
00:20:08,741 --> 00:20:10,741
    WHAT'S WRONG                
 WITH YOUR GLASSES?             

463
00:20:10,743 --> 00:20:12,743
     THEY DON'T HAVE LENSES     
            ANYMORE.            

464
00:20:12,745 --> 00:20:16,214
 I HAVEN'T NEEDED ACTUAL GLASSES
       FOR ALMOST A YEAR.       

465
00:20:16,216 --> 00:20:19,550
       WHAT? YOUR EYESIGHT      
   JUST MAGICALLY GOT BETTER?   

466
00:20:19,552 --> 00:20:20,985
        YES!                    

467
00:20:20,987 --> 00:20:23,554
  I'VE BEEN DEALING             
WITH MAGIC AND MONSTERS         

468
00:20:23,556 --> 00:20:26,490
AND THINGS LIKE THESE           
 SINCE I MET STEVEN.            

469
00:20:26,492 --> 00:20:30,494
THAT'S WHY I NEED YOU TO BELIEVE
         I KNOW WHAT TO DO HERE.

470
00:20:30,496 --> 00:20:31,929
     BUT YOU --                 

471
00:20:31,931 --> 00:20:34,599
                    UGH!        
       THERE'S NO TIME FOR THIS.

472
00:20:34,601 --> 00:20:35,700
                   READY?       

473
00:20:35,702 --> 00:20:37,168
  DROP THE BUBBLE.              

474
00:20:38,438 --> 00:20:41,239
         [ SCREECHING ]         

475
00:20:41,241 --> 00:20:43,374
               HA!              
                       [ GASPS ]

476
00:20:43,376 --> 00:20:45,409
    [ GRUNTING ]                

477
00:20:50,850 --> 00:20:53,150
           [ WHOOSH ]           

478
00:20:59,759 --> 00:21:00,925
      [ CRICKETS CHIRPING ]     

479
00:21:00,927 --> 00:21:02,760
    SO THAT'S WHY               
  IT HAD NO PULSE.              

480
00:21:02,762 --> 00:21:04,295
  GEM EXPERIMENTS.              

481
00:21:04,297 --> 00:21:06,464
    THIS IS WHAT                
 YOU'VE BEEN DOING?             

482
00:21:06,466 --> 00:21:10,368
  TRAINING TO FIGHT             
   THESE...THINGS?              

483
00:21:10,370 --> 00:21:11,135
              AAH!              

484
00:21:11,137 --> 00:21:12,803
                    SORRY,      
               DR. MAHESHWAREN. 

485
00:21:12,805 --> 00:21:15,139
               THAT'S MY LION.  

486
00:21:15,141 --> 00:21:18,442
           MOM, I'M REALLY SORRY
             ABOUT LYING TO YOU.

487
00:21:18,444 --> 00:21:20,444
               IT STARTED OFF   
              AS A TINY SECRET, 

488
00:21:20,446 --> 00:21:22,980
           AND THEN IT FELT LIKE
            IF I DIDN'T HIDE IT,

489
00:21:22,982 --> 00:21:26,050
  YOU WOULDN'T LET ME SEE STEVEN
                 EVER AGAIN.    

490
00:21:26,052 --> 00:21:29,720
IS THAT HOW YOU FEEL?           
ARE WE TOO CONTROLLING?         

491
00:21:29,722 --> 00:21:31,155
                   MAYBE.       

492
00:21:31,157 --> 00:21:33,224
 I JUST WANTED TO BE            
   A GOOD MOTHER.               

493
00:21:33,226 --> 00:21:35,926
   I-I JUST WANTED              
   TO PROTECT YOU.              

494
00:21:35,928 --> 00:21:38,929
       I CAN PROTECT MYSELF NOW.

495
00:21:38,931 --> 00:21:42,466
      [ SIGHS ]                 

496
00:21:42,468 --> 00:21:43,634
        OKAY.                   

497
00:21:44,270 --> 00:21:46,270
   WE'LL PULL BACK              
    ON THE RULES,               

498
00:21:46,272 --> 00:21:48,406
AND I'LL TRY TO KEEP            
    AN OPEN MIND                

499
00:21:48,408 --> 00:21:53,077
 ABOUT THIS AND THAT            
     AND...HIM.                 

500
00:21:54,480 --> 00:21:56,681
    IT SCARES ME                
THAT YOU CAN'T TALK TO ME.      

501
00:21:56,683 --> 00:21:59,350
   I NEED TO KNOW               
WHAT'S HAPPENING IN YOUR LIFE.  

502
00:21:59,352 --> 00:22:02,620
  I NEED TO STEP IN             
WHEN YOU'RE IN OVER YOUR HEAD.  

503
00:22:02,622 --> 00:22:06,023
WILL YOU JUST PROMISE ME        
YOU'LL STOP ALL THIS LYING?     

504
00:22:06,025 --> 00:22:08,759
               THAT'S A RULE.   

505
00:22:08,761 --> 00:22:10,761
 I LOVE YOU, HONEY.             

506
00:22:10,763 --> 00:22:13,064
            I LOVE YOU TOO, MOM.

507
00:22:23,109 --> 00:22:25,376
       ♪ I ALWAYS THOUGHT       
        I MIGHT BE BAD ♪        

508
00:22:25,378 --> 00:22:28,446
 ♪ NOW I'M SURE THAT IT'S TRUE ♪

509
00:22:28,448 --> 00:22:32,049
        ♪ 'CAUSE I THINK        
        YOU'RE SO GOOD ♪        

510
00:22:32,051 --> 00:22:34,719
  ♪ AND I'M NOTHING LIKE YOU ♪  

